    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect UE counting in eNB scope thread\n\n### Summary\nThe `scope_thread_eNB()` function in the LTE eNB softscope implementation had a logic error in how it counted UEs when processing multiple component carriers. The bug caused the scope to display data for fewer UEs than configured when `MAX_NUM_CCs` was greater than 1.\n\nThe issue occurred because the UE counter `ue_cnt` was incremented inside the component carrier loop instead of the UE loop, leading to premature termination of UE processing.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/lte_enb_scope.c`: Fixed nested loop logic in `scope_thread_eNB()` to properly count UEs and process all configured CCs per UE.\n\nUnder high load with multiple UEs and CCs active, this would cause only the first few UEs to have their scope data updated, while the rest would be ignored. The fix ensures all `scope_enb_num_ue` configured UEs are processed regardless of CC count.\n"
}